        public boolean setExercise(java.lang.String _name,
                           java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> _questions,
                           java.util.ArrayList _answers,
                           boolean _isCloze,
                           CMember _member)
        This method adds the given exercise to the exercises list of the course. Only the administrator of the course is allowed to add exercises.
        Parameters:
        _name - Character string that represents the name of this exercise
        _questions - Array of character strings that represents the questions
        _answers - Array of character strings that represents the answers
        _isCloze - Boolean to identify the kind of this exercise, according to this an instance of CCloze or CMultipleChoice will be created
        _member - Member that is calling this method, required to validate if it is the administrator
        Returns:
        True or false depending on whether the exercise has been added successful

      • controlExercise

        public float controlExercise(CExercise _exercise,
                             java.util.ArrayList _answers)
        With this method each member of the course is able to get its exercises checked automatically. If the given exercise does not exist in the exercises list of the course it returns the invalid value -2. Else it calls the appropriate control-method of the exercise by checking which kind of exercise it is.
        Parameters:
        _exercise - Exercise that has to be checked
        _answers - Array of either character strings or boolean that will be compared with the correct answers
        Returns:
        Float value that represents the result achieved

      • setMaterial

        public boolean setMaterial(java.lang.String _title,
                           java.lang.String _fileType,
                           CMember _member)
                    throws java.io.IOException
        This method provides the opportunity to upload each kind of files as additional information to the courses topic. The files to be uploaded has to be located in the callers home directory. Only the administrator of the course is allowed to upload files.
        It uses the helper function "readFile" to create a byte array that serves as input for the output stream. If the file has been uploaded successful this method creates a new instance of CMaterial with the appropriate attributes and adds it to the material list of the course.
        Parameters:
        _title - Array of character strings that represents the name of the material
        _fileType - Character string to identify which kind of file has to be created
        _member - Member who is calling this method, required to validate if it is the administrator
        Returns:
        True or false depending on whether the material has been uploaded successful
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - If an input or output exception occurred
        java.io.FileNotFoundException - If the given file does not exist in the callers home directory

      • removeMaterial

        public boolean removeMaterial(CMaterial _material,
                              CMember _member)
        This method removes the given material from the material list of the course. Only the administrator of the course is allowed to remove material. It returns false either if the given member is not the administrator of the course or the given material does not exist in the material list of the course. The server administrator is responsible for deleting unnecessary files on the server.
        Parameters:
        _material - Material that has to be deleted
        _member - Member who is calling this method, required to validate if it is the administrator
        Returns:
        True or false depending on whether the material has been deleted successful
